document_data.History:
Prior to {{yearlink|1357}}, Fimril was Fimril of [[Westgate]], strongly implying he'd spent a significant amount of time in that city. He'd spent at least one year, per his own recollection, developing a spell that created an all-devouring shield of darkness, capable of stopping most spells and disintegrating most material that it went through.

He was part of a meeting in late {{yearlink|1357}}, in which Sarhthor offered several magelings of the Zhentarim the assignment to hunt down [[Shandril Shessair]] for her spellfire.{{cite book/Crown of Fire/TPB 2002|105-106|5}}

Though he captured Shandril Shessair, he used a killing spell on [[Mirt]] when the latter turned up to rescue her; the spell was reflected, slaying him.
